𝐋𝐞𝐭 𝐡𝐚𝐩𝐩𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐬 𝐛𝐮𝐛𝐛𝐥𝐞 𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐫 💛 
Once upon a time, bubbles enjoyed a life that did justice to her name better. This didn't last for long though, because she was bitten by a dog at barely 2 months of age. This caused a spinal compression and led to huge gaps in her spine. As a result of this injury, her limbs lost all sensation, requiring her to drag her body to move ahead. A couple of months ago, we trained her to use a wheel cart to help with movement and noticed that she was sporadically lifting her hind legs to support her body. This gave us hope and we started physiotherapy sessions for her at Max vets, of which she has already undergone 7 sessions and is showing signs of improvement. 

The slightest chance of Bubbles walking again has made us put our heart and soul into seeing it come true. But we need your help to see this through, as each session costs us nearly INR 3,000 and we are aiming to raise funds for at least 10 more sessions. Together, let us get bubbles back to the life she had before. To help us with her physio sessions, Google Pay or Paytm us at the number - 8826299270

#helpnow #donatetoday #donatetoday #donatefordogs #pauseforpaws #donationappeal #livethetale #waggingtales

None of the dogs that grow up on the streets have a trouble-free life. This gets exponentially worse with the ageing of street animals, making old dogs one of the most vulnerable beings out there. We're doing our best to make sure they are cared for, and you could pitch in. Through #AdoptFromHome you can choose to #VirtuallyAdopt a #SeniorDog making sure that the older animals on the streets get to live the rest of their life in peace and dignity.

#virtualadoption #virtualparenting #virtualparent

𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐓𝐡𝐫𝐞𝐞 𝐌𝐮𝐬𝐤𝐞𝐭𝐞𝐞𝐫𝐬 💛 

Sometimes fate can take the form of human recklessness . At least that's how these three met. All of them were victims of hit and run. We believe that in such scenarios, the "hit" might be an accident, but "run" never is. It is a choice. It is cowardice.

Divya and Mishti had to get amputations, while Rani hobbles as a direct aftermath of their accidents. But nothing could touch their resolve or dampen their spirit. Always ready to mingle with new people and dogs alike, they're a delight to be around. Their energy is infectious, lighting up every room they're in. Now they're all looking for homes to light up and spread their love. Diva and Rani are both 1 year old, vaccinated and spayed. Mishti is 4.5 months old and vaccinated.

Help us find them a forever home!

#adoptdontshop #adoptnow

We spotted Diva while returning from a feeding round. She was struggling to cross a busy road, with her hind legs almost dysfunctional. When we tried approaching her, she wasn't willing to let us anywhere near her. After a lot of resistance and persuasion, we were finally able to get her to the vet, as she slept soundly on the way after all that struggle. She was severely malnourished with ribs visible through the skin, dehydrated, and carrying bite marks all over her body. 
Her hind leg had to be amputated and it took a while for her vitals to be stabilized. At this point, she absolutely detested human touch, crawling to a corner when anyone approached. But with a lot of love and care, Diva is happily hopping around, making friends amongst the other dogs and slowly getting used to us being around. 
Her story has been one of a heartening turnaround, and what she needs now on this journey is a virtual parent. Someone who can #AdoptFromHome , sponsoring her living expenses remotely. DM us if you are interested in being Diva's virtual parent. 

#virtualAdoption #virtualparenting #adopt #adoptnow #virtualparents #adoptfromhome

latestIgtvVideos.title: The story behind Dairy products
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Do we ever wonder how many lives are sacrificed behind a pouch of milk or a tiny ice cream. We never do, right. Oh, they come from big renowned factories with thousands of healthy cows and buffaloes, we say. But is it so? This is a #repost from @pfa.official . Imagine if this was your new born baby and if they were deprived of their mother's milk. Neither the baby nor the mother could survive. We are the most intelligent animals on the planet who could speak for ourselves and take stand for something. This does not give us the right to do whatever we can with the helpless animals. It's high time now we stand against cruelty. It's never too late to change something and bring a revolution. Say #no to dairy products. Go #vegan .
If you want to lend us your helping hand and be a partner in our mission of saving these voiceless stray animals, you can donate via the link on our bio.

Presenting our little champion Bubbles 🧿💜

Thank you Swapnil for rescuing Bubbles and helping her 🙏. Bubble’s came to us after being attacked by an older dog when she was barely 2 months old . She had suffered severe spinal compression and injuries causing big gaps in her spine . The first few days were really difficult for her . The doctors suggested a spinal surgery with little hope , but her tiny body wasn’t in a condition to take that chance . She survived parvo and UTI in the months to follow. After her condition stabilised , the kindest @pooch_tales helped us fundraise for her cart made by @happycaninecarts . 

Sharing this little happiness with you all that made it possible 🙏🙏🙏

#rescuedogsofinstagram  #dogs #specialdog  #dogswithwheels  #instareels

Will you donate and help our doggos start Jan 2024 on a happy note ?🥺😊🫶 #jan2025 

Once again we are stepping into the new year with a hope of ensuring all these bellies are filled with fresh warm meals  every single day so life can be a little less harsh for them on the streets . 

Gentle reminder that your contribution of Rs 500/month (6 USD)  to our #FoodRaiser covers the food expenses of a community dog/ cat for an entire month. We feed nearly 500 plus community dogs and cats in areas of South and Central Delhi everyday and over 400 of them at our two rescue shelters  in Ghitorni and Gwalpahari .

The #foodraiser aims to find sponsors for atleast half of them🙏 every month .

You can also choose to sponsor a meal at our rescue centre for all our shelter doggos in Ghitorni for Rs 2500 ( 31 USD). 

This is our main fundraiser every month and we have the additional responsibility of running two shelters on our shoulders , which is a safe recovery space for so many injured , sick , abandoned , old dogs . Through your donations , big or small , please consider helping us out for the month of August 🙏

Hi Everyone, i am Rose. I am around 1 years old(my foster mom thinks so, but i am more matured than a 1yr old but anyways) Neutered, leash trained, pee potty trained, dewormed, vaccinated and currently at a foster home. I was being attacked by bigger dogs because a lady relocated me from my area and brought me in my foster parents area. They brought me home, gave me medicines and love that i craved for...Now i am ready for my furrever parents who can give me lots of cuddles and scritches(endless). I can be a wonderful companion to you and your fur babies. I have excellent temperament, love to cuddle and sleep for long hours. I currently share the space with 2 foster sisters and they really love me and i them(i am really lovable i think) I am a good girl and i will be happy if you welcome me into your home and hearts❤️❤️ Will you adopt me???

✨Important notice ✨

Kindly note , the shelter will not be taking any visitors till Feb 15 2025 . We are currently amidst shifting shelters , and construction work at our new shelter leaving us with no time for visitor management . 

We are also highly understaffed so have been taking in only extremely critical medical cases so for boarding needs , non critical medical cases etc please reach out to other shelters until we are in a position to resume work at full swing 🙏

In addition , no ABC ( animal birth control ) surgeries will be scheduled at the shelter until our OT has been set up at the new shelter in Gwalpahari . 

Hoping to see you all soon 🩷

Not all Santas🎅wear pants , some wear sarees too 😁♥️

A Merry Christmas to everyone from our badass Santa . Remember to be kind to animals , to be compassionate and most importantly to do what you love to do without caring about the bullies . I hope we all find the courage to stand up for what’s right and never let people’s negativity get into the way of your good deeds 🩷

Here’s my 62 year old mama , who has been feeding community animals for over 7 years now wishing you a Merry Christmas in her own style and sass . Let’s show the world it’s cool to be kind after all 😁

[merry Christmas , it’s cool to be kind , community animals , feeder , love dogs , Santa in a saree ]

It takes a special hooman to see what a special dog truly is capable of 🩷 

Two years since @diva_divinski flew to her forever home with her hoomans and every day is just a reminder of her resilience and her zest for life . Found scavenging on the steeets of India by her amazing hooman Aina , her story gives so many rescued shelter dogs with special needs hope of a better future 🩷

I hope and pray more dogs like Diva continue to find their special hoomans in 2025 🧿🫶

SOS medical fundraiser for Jugni and Goldie 🙏

As the year ends our shelter is experiencing a surge of medical cases but we are ending the year on a note of gratitude knowing so many lives this year were saved thanks to the kindness and generosity of the community we have built . 

Here are these two girls , Jugni and Goldie , both community dogs that needed urgent medical support this month for their tumour surgeries who could really use your help 🙏.
We are raising 28,000 Rs ( 330 USD ) for their medical expenses which includes : 

Tumor removal surgery : 6k each ( Rs 12000) 
Two blood tests each (pre and post surgery ) : Rs 5000
Biopsy ( for both ) : Rs 3000 ( the vet thinks Jugni’s tumour can be cancerous , but we need to be sure ) 
Post operative care ( 10 days each for both ) : Rs 8000

Please consider donating for these girls and helping us out . All donations made to our Indian account are tax exempted under 80G and 12A. Overseas donors can donate via Milaap ( link is in our bio- pay for paws ).

The one where a shelter dog went home ✨🩷

Chhaya came to us last year for treatment after @divisha.222 found her in a miserable state near her vet’s clinic . She was clearly abandoned and one could see the dejection and sadness in her eyes . She refused to eat for days and that when she was picked for treatment. Her blood values were all over the place and she spent months in recovery . Despite her struggles she was always one of the sweetest kids around and when this year @tanviakanksha walked into our shelter wishing to adopt a dog , Chhaya was on the top of our mind . As destiny would have it she went home after almost 14 months of being at the shelter and get to start a life again 🩷

Shelter dogs come with a lot of stigma and adult dogs are rarely people’s first choice when they choose to adopt so Chhaya ‘s happy story is a beacon of hope for so many of our shelter dogs to whom life hasn’t been so fair . Here’s to wishing 2025 being kind and giving shelter dogs a chance they deserve 🩷

Introducing AKIRA! 🖤

Akira is a gorgeous 2 month old desi girl, found without a mother or her litter mates in a forest in Uttarakhand. She was then brought to Delhi in hopes of a family and we hope you give her a chance. 🥹 Her vaccinations are underway and she’s a total cuddle bug. If you can foster her till we work on her adoption, please Dm us. Minimum foster period is 1 month. If you’d like to give her a forever home, drop us a message🤍
